I'm currently in the Defensive Security section (Cyber Security 101 > Defensive Security) and it's been fun so far! It's been mostly introduction, but it's still cool to kind of see things at work.

This room covered the basics of Digital Forensics, using technology to investigate crimes fully and hopefully help to solve them. It covered tools and techniques, as well as several observations that might be helpful for someone intersted in entering the digital forensics field.

